title: A.J. Brown is averaging a career-low 1.3 yards per route run this season, averaging at least double that in every other season of his career.
subNote1: Brown has also been targeted on just 24.5% of his routes, his lowest since his rookie season in 2019 (23.3%) and 4.3% lower than his target rate as an Eagle entering this season (28.8%). Even when targeted, Brown has averaged just -0.09 EPA per target, 6th-lowest among 42 pass catchers with at least 30 targets.

title: Outside of Week 2, where Russell Wilson completed 7 of 11 passes over 20 air yards for 264 yards, 3 touchdowns, and an interception against the Cowboys, the Giants have failed to complete any of their 15 other deep pass attempts as a team this season (3 INT).
subNote1: Jaxson Dart specifically has specifically gone 0 for 8 on deep pass attempts (INT), the most deep pass attempts without a completion by any quarterback this season (Wilson: 7 for 18). Matchup: The Eagles defense has allowed just five deep completions this season, but four of the five have resulted in touchdowns, 2nd-most in the NFL.

title: After leading the NFL with 829 rushing yards before contact last season (207 more than any running back since at least 2017), Saquon Barkley has totaled just 47 rushing yards before contact this season, 27th-most among running backs.
subNote1: Barkley has also struggled after contact, averaging just 2.7 yards after contact per carry, 5th-fewest among 34 running backs with at least 40 carries. In 2024, Barkley averaged 3.4 yards after contact per carry (NFL average: 3.3). Matchup: The Giants defense has allowed the 10th-most rushing yards before contact (1.1) and most rushing yards after contact (4.5) to running backs this season.
